<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=20 COLS=75 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by Risini Visinimi:
[I]Hi All!

I don't like to run arround alone, but I even like it to have only one Char. to identify with. *stupitthinking*

I know that normaly the one disagree with the other, but I think almost everyone knows the system of fallout ?!? There it was managed pretty well I think! I always feard my Char or even one of the people accompaning me 'll die. But it wasn't inpossible to manage the game without this guys.

In imaging of the fact, that you 'll not be able to do everything, I think that hepls to identify with the Char. Why must he/she be able to do everything? If you play a thief he would try to do everthing "backwards". If you play with a fighter he would make almost everything by using violence. It you play a mage he would try to manage the problems with magic. And so on......

The "only" problem with that is that you must be able to manage a problem by diffrent ways. There the exp. should even depend on the class. If the thief would kill everybody in an open fight, to get an item, he 'll get less exp. than a fighter doing this.
For posibilitys, each char. can [f]try[/f]:

Mage: make invisiblbe, take the thing teleport away.

fighter: kill everybody or intimidate the NPCs, that they 'll give you the item.

Thief: sneak to the thing, steal it and seak away without beeing seen.

If a Char. would manage a other way then his, he would not get the full exp., 'cause he did it not like a char. of this kind would do it.

If somebody wants there could be an universal char. whitch wont manage anything realy good (even at the end ;-) ). He would get an average exp. but never the higest amount. There schould be still different amouts of exp. for each quest, 'cause normaly some things are done one way better, but with this bonus/malus system even the not perfect way could be the best for this calss (But i doesn't need to). At the end all exp. bonus/malus wont help one class to riese faster.

But I get away from the point. ;-) It youst wanished in my mind and I didn't want to open a new topic for it. ;-)

So You 'll have only one char to akt realy with, even if you can give some simple orders to your company.

That is what I think will be the best.

By Risini Visínimi[/I][/QUOTE]

