na, Arial">To be honest: I don't care about it.<P>Both has big advantages. This 'superhero' point is very weak. I have never seen any crpg player not trying to get most out of his solo pc or party members. Perhaps there may be one or two, but they are the exception, not the rule.<P>I have never had a feeling during any game as great as in Ultima Underworld I + II. You had your ONE character and a story around it. It has been a great game. <P>In such games you can indentify yourself with the character. I can't do this when playing with a party of four or six. One could even argue this is no rpg at all cause you don't play <B>your</B> character, but it is much fun too.<P>I have never played a crpg twice with the exception of wizardry 7 though. I have loved this game though it is party based and asks for a change of class now and then (only to get you characters better).<P>Both are typical games for single or party and the first one has real time combat and the party thing some phased/turn based combat.<P>I can't understand those guys telling: we need this combat system or we won't play. This is rgp, not some simple action game with a score in the upper left corner of the screen.<P>IMHO it is the game itself, the story, the feeling during the game. We all know we need to fight now and then and perhaps even like it, but it should not be the motivation to play such a game, else you should look for games like Diablo, Darkstone or Nox.<P>In a rpg you have your character developing while it is experincing the story and its twist, lots of puzzles and quests, enjoying npcs running around and telling you weird stuff. This is not some hunt for the ultimate character with the ultimate weapon found in one of 6-20 randomized dungeons.<P>I like those games too (never played anything more than diablo)but those are different and should stay that way.<P>So I don't think the combat system is the key to a crpg, may be a part like graphic and sound but not the key. I am patient to see what project C will show us, since I know we will have multiplayer support  <IMG SRC="http://www.larian.com/ubb/wink.gif"> (no not internet, I don't like kids trying to show you how great there characters are...)<P>I play with a couple of friends in a lan which is even more fun than playing a single character.<P>Goemoe</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Renyx</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Realtime is an evolution ... all games used to be turn based, now all games are realtime. This doesn't mean a realtime RPG has to be all hack and slash, it can be just as tactical as a turn based RPG.<P>About the party, I agree with Konradt. You play as a single character but there could be a group of people who joins you for a special quest, or even a war like that example in one of the screenshots. <P>To Konradt :<BR>&gt;&gt;Because of the joint inventory, One person could spend all the money, without consent.<P>Wasn't that you who spended all our money and ruined the game  <IMG SRC="http://www.larian.com/ubb/smile.gif"> <P>Renyx</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Goemoe</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">It's not much of an evolution. It is just that the hardware has come to a level where it can manage some realtime situations it couldn't some years ago. There are still things better handled in turn/phase based mode because we(human) can only comprehend and manage a limited amount of things at the same time. <P>There are always some people faster acting und managing things than other, but you have to do it for the mass not the single one.<P>I know some guys who are excellent opponents for strategy games, but they need to think about some things for quite some (awful boring  <IMG SRC="http://www.larian.com/ubb/wink.gif">) time. They wouldn't play any RTS because they cannot handle it, but they are quite tough opponents in any turnbased game.<P>There will be turnbased games as long as there will be games at all. Realtime is only one possible way but certainly no evolution.<P>I can't think of realtime combat system for a party. You would have to depend on scripts but they can only do what the developers provide unless you are able to write your own scripts and this is a point most won't or can't.<P>I would prefer a realtime system for only one, but not for more.<P>Goemoe</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Goemoe</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I think Larian would write some CRPG history if they manage to implement both systems.<P>My current favorite game is Age of Wonders (really great fantasy strategy - a mix of warlords, mom and own features!) which allows to choose between tactical combat screen and unit to unit auto combat, which works far better than the normal 'auto combat' system many games offer.<P>I am getting to be a great fan of this choice, because I use both and I always like to have a choice  <IMG SRC="http://www.larian.com/ubb/wink.gif"><P>Goemoe</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">lar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Yeah Arhu, I was waiting for this one to show it's little head all by itself  <IMG SRC="http://www.larian.com/ubb/wink.gif"> I even got some emails regarding the topic  <IMG SRC="http://www.larian.com/ubb/wink.gif"><P>The avi should show the system we're going for. It's real time, but I hope we're managing to implement enough strategy in there. Ultimately however that's the job of the AI. If it's good enough, and the play is balanced enough, you won't make it by just hacking and slashing.  (Although occasionally I do enjoy a good hack and slash moment). Further, as I already said, story plays a very important role in 'Project C'.  <P>Lar</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Bronthion</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Ok lar,<P>realtime it is! <P>But is there a pause option like in BG?  <IMG SRC="http://www.larian.com/ubb/biggrin.gif"> Where you can halt the game and choose your weapon, spell, healing potion, etc. Or is it Diablo style, where you can't do such things?  <IMG SRC="http://www.larian.com/ubb/frown.gif"><P><P>------------------<BR>Bronthion, der dunkle Halb-Elf<BR>Bronthion, the dark Half-Elf<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Lord_Konradt</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">hi,<P>hehe I know Renyx.<P>Grietz,<BR>Lord_Konradt</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
